I like the trick in Golang marketing, where we get a code full of references to some libraries. Same could be done about other languages.<p>Oh, look, web server in 5 lines of code, in Java!<p><pre><code>    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Server server = new Server(80);
        server.setHandler(new HelloWorld());

        server.start();
        server.join();
    }
</code></pre>
The trick is cheap, but it works!
